      <dc:title>Handwritten postcard from Schenker to Violin, postmarked November 27,
        1933</dc:title>

      <dcterms:created>1933-11-27T12:00:00Z</dcterms:created>
      <dcterms:dateSubmitted>2022-02-12</dcterms:dateSubmitted>
      <dc:description>In a message deprecating Hoboken’s character, Schenker believes that Hoboken
        (the “wandering Dutchman") is trying to stretch out his tuition by paying social calls with
        his wife outside lesson times; he likes Vienna because the cost of living is lower than in
        Holland.</dc:description>
      <dc:subject/>



      <marcrel:correspondent key="entity-000632">HSchenker</marcrel:correspondent>
